# Appendix E. Comparison with Kuzborskij and Cesa-Bianchi (2020) 

Let $f \in \mathscr{C}^{\alpha}(\mathcal{X}, L),\left(M^{(k)}\right)_{1 \leqslant k \leqslant \mathrm{~d}\left(\mathcal{T}_{0}\right)}$ such that $M^{(k)} \geqslant L_{n}(f)$ for any $n \in \mathcal{N}\left(\mathcal{T}_{0}\right), \mathrm{d}(n)=k$ and $T^{(k)}=\left\{1 \leqslant t \leqslant T: x_{t} \in \mathcal{X}_{n}, \mathrm{~d}(n)=k\right\}$. Let $\mathcal{T}$ be any pruning and let $\alpha=1, d=1$. We have for the squared (exp-concave) loss, according to Corollary 1 :

$$
\begin{aligned}
\operatorname{Reg}_{T}(f) & \lesssim \sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T})} \min \left\{\left(L_{n}(f) \frac{\left|\mathcal{X}_{n}\right|}{|\mathcal{X}|}\right)^{\frac{2}{3}}\left|T_{n}\right|^{\frac{1}{3}},\left(L_{n}(f) \frac{\left|\mathcal{X}_{n}\right|}{|\mathcal{X}|}\right)^{\frac{1}{3}}\left|T_{n}\right|^{\frac{1}{6}}\right\} \\
& =\sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} \sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=k} \min \left\{\left(L_{n}(f) \frac{\left|\mathcal{X}_{n}\right|}{|\mathcal{X}|}\right)^{\frac{2}{3}}\left|T_{n}\right|^{\frac{1}{3}},\left(L_{n}(f) \frac{\left|\mathcal{X}_{n}\right|}{|\mathcal{X}|}\right)^{\frac{1}{3}}\left|T_{n}\right|^{\frac{1}{3}}\right\} \\
& \leqslant \sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} \min \left\{\left(\sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=k} L_{n}(f) 2^{-k}\right)^{\frac{2}{3}}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{1}{3}},\left(\sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=k} L_{n}(f) 2^{-k}\right)^{\frac{1}{2}}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{1}{2}}\right\} \\
& \leqslant \sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} \min \left\{\left.\left(M^{(k)} w^{(k)}\right)^{\frac{2}{3}}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{1}{3}},\left(M^{(k)} w^{(k)}\right)^{\frac{1}{3}}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{1}{2}}\right\}\right. \\
& \leqslant \min \left\{(\bar{M}(f))^{\frac{2}{3}} T^{\frac{1}{3}},(\bar{M}(f) T)^{\frac{1}{2}}\right\}
\end{aligned}
$$

where $\bar{M}(f)=\sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} w^{(k)} M^{(k)}$ with $w^{(k)}=\sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=k} \frac{\left|\mathcal{X}_{n}\right|}{|\mathcal{X}|}=2^{-k} \mid\left\{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=\right.$ $k\} \mid$ the proportion of leaves in $\mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T})$ at level $k$ in $\mathcal{N}\left(\mathcal{T}_{0}\right)$ and where we applied Hölder's inequality to get (46) and (47). The last upper-bound recovers and improves the one of Kuzborskij and Cesa-Bianchi (2020) for dimension $d=1$, as described in the main part of the paper. For higher dimension $d \geqslant 2$, both for exp-concave and convex losses, Theorem 2 gives for any pruning $\mathcal{T}$ and any function $f \in \mathscr{C}^{1}(\mathcal{X}, L)$ (ignoring the dependence on $\mathcal{X})$ :

$$
\begin{aligned}
\operatorname{Reg}_{T}(f) \lesssim \sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T})} L_{n}(f)\left|T_{n}\right|^{1-\frac{1}{d}} & =\sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} \sum_{n \in \mathcal{L}(\mathcal{T}): \mathrm{d}(n)=k} L_{n}(f)\left|T_{n}\right|^{\frac{d-1}{d}} \\
& \leqslant \sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{d}(\mathcal{T})} M^{(k)}|\{n: \mathrm{d}(n)=k\}|^{\frac{1}{d}}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{d-1}{d}}
\end{aligned}
$$

which grows as $O\left(\sum_{k} M^{(k)}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{d-1}{d}}\right)$ compared to $O\left(\sum_{k}\left(M^{(k)}\left|T^{(k)}\right|\right)^{\frac{d}{d+1}}\right)$ in Kuzborskij and Cesa-Bianchi (2020). As a consequence, if for every level $k=1, \ldots, \mathrm{~d}(\mathcal{T}), M^{(k)}\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{d-1}{d}} \geqslant\left(M^{(k)}\left|T^{(k)}\right|\right)^{\frac{d}{d+1}}$ it turns out that $M^{(k)} \geqslant\left|T^{(k)}\right|^{\frac{1}{d}}$ which leads to an equivalent bound $O\left(\sum_{k}\left|T^{(k)}\right|\right)=O(T)$ which corresponds to the worst case regret bound (42). As a conclusion, our bound recovers and improves their results in particular with a dependence to lower constants $L_{n}(f)$ and lower time rate $\left|T_{n}\right|^{1-\frac{1}{d}}$.
